From 423580b39704b65ded63fa113b5361f35e41a2bd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Christian Hewitt <christianshewitt@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 09:47:21 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 33/39] WIP: media: tuners: r848: add default case in
 R848_SysFreq_Sel standard switch

The switch on R848_Standard only adjusts AGC_CLK for the DVB-T2
variants; every other standard keeps the value assigned just before the
switch. Add an explicit default: break; to document this and silence the
-Wswitch warning about the many unhandled enumeration values.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Signed-off-by: Christian Hewitt <christianshewitt@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/media/tuners/r848.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/media/tuners/r848.c b/drivers/media/tuners/r848.c
index 96318070ea2f..1bd7f77047f4 100644
--- a/drivers/media/tuners/r848.c
+++ b/drivers/media/tuners/r848.c
@@ -3465,6 +3465,8 @@ static R848_SysFreq_Info_Type R848_SysFreq_Sel(struct r848_priv *priv,
 				R848_SysFreq_Info.AGC_CLK =
 					0x1C; //250Hz   R26[4:2]
 				break;
+			default:
+				break;
 			}
 		}
 		break;
-- 
